Every single trade has been getting BLOCKED since the identity-check
merge (c517f72/9885213), not just NATGAS. Root cause: open_position()'s
pre-flight identity check falls back to comparing the instrument_id
itself (as a string) against the live API symbol when no symbol is
passed:

    _symbol_for_preflight = symbol or str(instrument_id)

execution_worker.py's only call to open_position() never passed
symbol=, despite already having it available as a local variable
(symbol = trade.get('symbol', str(instrument_id)), set earlier in the
same loop). Confirmed via live error logs — instrument_id=22 correctly
resolves to 'NATGAS' on the live API, but the check compared it against
'22' (the fallback), not 'NATURAL -USD' (the trade's actual local
symbol) — proving symbol was empty/unset at the call site, not that
the mapping itself was wrong.

This was not caught by RoBoCop's earlier live verification because
those tests called verify_instrument_identity() directly with an
explicit expected_symbol argument, never exercising the real
production call path (execution_worker → open_position) where the
argument was missing entirely.

Fix: pass symbol=symbol in execution_worker.py's open_position() call.
Confirmed via grep this is the ONLY call site of open_position() in the
entire codebase, so this fix is complete — no other callers need it.

⚠️ Separate, narrower issue NOT fixed here: instrument_id=22's actual
stored symbol in the live trading.db appears to be 'NATURAL -USD'
(from the Discord trade title), while eToro's live API calls it
'NATGAS'. These do not match under the existing suffix-only
normalization (_normalize_symbol_for_comparison only strips -USD/-/USD,
not synonym differences like NATURAL vs NATGAS). Once this fix is live,
NATGAS trades specifically may still correctly block until that local
naming is corrected or an alias mapping is added — this needs a live
DB check (SELECT symbol FROM instruments WHERE instrument_id=22) since
the watchlist_multiasset/instruments seed data isn't in the repo.

Verified: 59/59 tests pass. Only one call site of open_position() exists
codebase-wide (confirmed via grep), so no other regressions of this
kind are present.
---
 src/bot/workers/execution_worker.py | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/bot/workers/execution_worker.py b/src/bot/workers/execution_worker.py
index 5412e3a..903416d 100644
--- a/src/bot/workers/execution_worker.py
+++ b/src/bot/workers/execution_worker.py
@@ -234,6 +234,7 @@ def main() -> None:
                     instrument_id=instrument_id,
                     amount_usd=amount_usd,
                     stop_loss_pct=stop_loss_pct,
+                    symbol=symbol,
                 )
     
                 # d1. BLOCKED path — open_position() returned a soft-block dict
